SIMPLE: underworld
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underworld
<hw>Un"der*world`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
lower of inferior world; the world which is under the heavens; the
earth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That overspreads (with such a reverence)⟦br⟧
This <qex>underworld</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The mythological place of departed souls;
Hades.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The portion of the world which is below the horizon;
the opposite side of the world; the antipodes.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fresh as the first beam glittering on a sail,⟦br⟧
That brings our friends up from the <qex>underworld</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The inferior part of mankind.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Atterbury.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underwrite</ent>⟦br⟧
